fault", "desc": "No Bug, mozilla-central repo-update HSTS HPKP remote-settings - a=repo-update r=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D13670", "files": ["security/manager/ssl/StaticHPKPins.h", "security/manager/ssl/nsSTSPreloadList.inc"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b41192e679458ff4fcea290f8dd06326fd828ca1", "parents": ["b46490e922b4b404359830f21aa1f01097201335"], "tags": []}, {"author": "WR Updater Bot \u003cgraphics-team@mozilla.staktrace.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1511660 - Update webrender to commit a1758f0fc17a71c8d53387be5e9da42495ee11ae (WR PR #3380). r=kats\n\nhttps://github.com/servo/webrender/pull/3380\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D13674", "files": ["gfx/webrender_bindings/revision.txt", "gfx/wr/wrench/Cargo.toml", "gfx/wr/wrench/src/main.rs", "gfx/wr/wrench/src/wrench.rs"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ccf502c02f51b2a3ab97a153902aa050a1b96cbc", "parents": ["b41192e679458ff4fcea290f8dd06326fd828ca1"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Martin Stransky \u003cstransky@redhat.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1511011 - Removed moz_container_move as it's not used, r=jhorak\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D13404", "files": ["widget/gtk/mozcontainer.cpp", "widget/gtk/mozcontainer.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "819a462d5dd04f30bc50b47d9e10930ae7b1c627", "parents": ["ccf502c02f51b2a3ab97a153902aa050a1b96cbc"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Martin Stransky \u003cstransky@redhat.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1511011 - Clean up wayland subsurface creation/management, r=jhorak\n\n- Don't create wl_subsurface in map event but rather when it's requested by compositor.\n- Don't create wl_surface at nsWindow::OnExposeEvent but check ready_to_draw instead.\n- Rename parent_surface_committed_handler to frame_clock_after_paint_handler.\n- Rename parent_surface_committed to ready_to_draw.\n- Rename needs_clear to surface_needs_clear.\n\nDepends on D13404\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D13405", "files": ["widget/gtk/mozcontainer.cpp", "widget/gtk/mozcontainer.h", "widget/gtk/nsWindow.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f349e5a7d515306dcfa5d0b9eb62f676873e8e78", "parents": ["819a462d5dd04f30bc50b47d9e10930ae7b1c627"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Daniel Stenberg \u003cdaniel@haxx.se\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "bug 1503393 - never let \"localhost\" get sent to a proxy r=mayhemer", "files": ["netwerk/base/nsProtocolProxyService.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "49428012434e379316f2d831a088a27cf1b429ee", "parents": ["f349e5a7d515306dcfa5d0b9eb62f676873e8e78"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Daniel Stenberg \u003cdaniel@haxx.se\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "bug 1503393 - verify default localhost not-proxied with PAC r=mayhemer", "files": ["netwerk/test/unit/test_protocolproxyservice.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "02e383b73c971e656097b3040e9cc523039018d6", "parents": ["49428012434e379316f2d831a088a27cf1b429ee"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Gijs Kruitbosch \u003cgijskruitbosch@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1503393 - Make 'no proxy' field editable r=jaws", "files": ["browser/components/preferences/connection.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7878029aaba609b5433d3eea98873a450cf2cb62", "parents": ["02e383b73c971e656097b3040e9cc523039018d6"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Daniel Stenberg \u003cdaniel@haxx.se\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "bug 1503393 - adjust tests for localhost proxying r=mayhemer\nFix test_proxy-failover_canceled and browser_firstPartyIsolation", "files": ["browser/components/originattributes/test/browser/browser_firstPartyIsolation.js", "netwerk/test/unit/test_proxy-failover_canceled.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "52e8ef71af9b837be53b294d09381d70c5efceba", "parents": ["7878029aaba609b5433d3eea98873a450cf2cb62"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Sebastian Hengst \u003carchaeopteryx@coole-files.de\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out 4 changesets (bug 1503393) for failing various browser-chrome tests, e.g. browser_extension_controlled.js. CLOSED TREE\n\nBacked out changeset 52e8ef71af9b (bug 1503393)\nBacked out changeset 7878029aaba6 (bug 1503393)\nBacked out changeset 02e383b73c97 (bug 1503393)\nBacked out changeset 49428012434e (bug 1503393)", "files": ["browser/components/originattributes/test/browser/browser_firstPartyIsolation.js", "browser/components/preferences/connection.js", "netwerk/base/nsProtocolProxyService.cpp", "netwerk/test/unit/test_protocolproxyservice.js", "netwerk/test/unit/test_proxy-failover_canceled.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7670b6ce33a4b3ad15ff3dc1ec3bfb9349cec19b", "parents": ["52e8ef71af9b837be53b294d09381d70c5efceba"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Martin Stransky \u003cstransky@redhat.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1491808 - Listen on window-state-event to set titlebar active/inactive state, r=jhorak\n\nThis is a workaround for https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/gtk/issues/1395\nGtk+ controls window active appearance by window-state-event signal\nbut gecko uses focus-in/out signals.\n\nSo we need to set the the titlebar state\nwhen window-state-event comes *after* focus-in/out signals.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D13051", "files": ["widget/gtk/nsNativeThemeGTK.cpp", "widget/gtk/nsWindow.cpp", "widget/gtk/nsWindow.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d1fc8c77ad7fc8098a798cb0df05587d7f374b95", "parents": ["7670b6ce33a4b3ad15ff3dc1ec3bfb9349cec19b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Martin Stransky \u003cstransky@redhat.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1491808 - [Linux/CSD/Titlebar] Force toplevel window repaint when titlebar rendering is enabled and its state changes, r=bzbarsky\n\nTitlebar (StyleAppearance::MozWindowTitlebar) style depends on toplevel window focus\nand we need to redraw it when toplevel window focus changes.\n\nUnfortunately according to https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/gtk/issues/1395\nthe toplevel window focus can't be used here as we can have active but unfocused\ntoplevel window during drag & drop.\n\nGtk+ controls window active appearance by window-state-event signal\nbut gecko uses focus-in/out signals, so we need to repaint the titlebar\nwhen window-state-event comes *after* focus-in/out signals.\n\nWe can't call mWidgetListener-\u003eWindowActivated() (and WindowDeactivated())\nas it was already called from focus-in/out handlers before window-state-event.\n\nDepends on D13051\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D13052", "files": ["widget/gtk/nsWindow.cpp", "widget/gtk/nsWindow.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1a6f9251c41f32feca557aa9f9ace21070bf803e", "parents": ["d1fc8c77ad7fc8098a798cb0df05587d7f374b95"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1511811 - Remove useless GECKO_BORROWED_TYPE_MUT.\n\nThis causes a typedef mozilla::ServoElementSnapshot ServoElementSnapshot; to be\ncreated, which we rely on bindgen not generating.\n\nBut bindgen will start (correctly) generating it in:\n\n  https://github.com/rust-lang/rust-bindgen/pull/1436\n\nSo easiest fix is just to remove this typedef, since it's just used by one FFI\nfunction.\n", "files": ["layout/style/BorrowedTypeList.h", "layout/style/GeckoBindings.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f5851346109d87c59d7389d3b8b25f2c02bd7d08", "parents": ["01d0813d8203d78613fc33a3e8e32627c1300b50"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Bastien Orivel \u003ceijebong@bananium.fr\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1511811 - Update syn and related dependencies. r=emilio\n", "files": ["servo/components/malloc_size_of_derive/Cargo.toml", "servo/co