}, {"author": "Jan de Mooij \u003cjdemooij@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1512417 - Pass |this| as second argument to Cu.import calls in Promise-backend.js to fix an issue with same-compartment realms. r=kmag\n\nWith same-compartment-realms, the Cu.import native is a cross-realm function so\nwe switch to its realm and ended up defining things on the wrong global.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D13905", "files": ["toolkit/modules/Promise-backend.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "52d8651b683dfcf944e72114a8a41878ce7d6c15", "parents": ["ae37561c3bf7cc9b83c4f5aad5cf4e28ed2e332c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Luca Greco \u003clgreco@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1512421 - contextMenus documentUrlPatterns should allow unrestricted schemes on privileged mozilla addons. r=mixedpuppy\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D13907", "files": ["browser/components/extensions/parent/ext-menus.js", "browser/components/extensions/test/browser/browser_ext_contextMenus_targetUrlPatterns.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2f5d2cc76b6b3f1c882c0211c95291e487953e29", "parents": ["52d8651b683dfcf944e72114a8a41878ce7d6c15"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Luca Greco \u003clgreco@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1512419 - Screenshots' contextMenu entry should be available on webpage in reader mode. r=_6a68\n\nDepends on D13907\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D13908", "files": ["browser/extensions/screenshots/background/main.js", "browser/extensions/screenshots/background/startBackground.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c28c5075d441e54eb4b4a5b5336374063544e676", "parents": ["2f5d2cc76b6b3f1c882c0211c95291e487953e29"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Thomas Daede \u003ctdaede@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1511223 - Update deb7 nasm to 2.13.01. r=glandium\n\nThis pulls a newer version of the nasm package, and patches\nout doc building in order to make it compile on debian 7.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D13510", "files": ["build/debian-packages/nasm-wheezy.diff", "taskcluster/ci/packages/kind.yml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "45cd802be3dd3d3271dc19a96e8a8adb7a73757e", "parents": ["c28c5075d441e54eb4b4a5b5336374063544e676"], "tags": []}, {"author": "rdalal \u003crdalal@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1504038 - Fix preference name styling on OS X on about:studies r=mythmon,Gijs\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D13877", "files": ["toolkit/components/normandy/content/about-studies/about-studies.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "68faf9528d57faadba69b18e883a3d291a504b5e", "parents": ["45cd802be3dd3d3271dc19a96e8a8adb7a73757e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Denis Palmeiro \u003cdpalmeiro@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1503251 - Keep payload values in the dictionary if they are still alive. r=djvj\n\nIf the JS::ResetTraceLogger() routine is called, then keep track of existing event payloads and keep their existence alive instead of clearing them.  This data can still be referred to in another profiler session and can therefore cause to dangling pointers if we free them.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D10277", "files": ["js/src/vm/TraceLogging.cpp", "js/src/vm/TraceLogging.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ec925f7dac88abd54ba19d4b317b7b3699ecce1f", "parents": ["68faf9528d57faadba69b18e883a3d291a504b5e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrei Lazar \u003candrei.a.lazar@softvision.ro\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1501024 WifiScanner should use ApplicationContext r=JanH\n\nFixed lint warning regarding memory leak inside WifiManager constructor.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D1