a8b09dd34ab398440fb"], "tags": []}], "date": 1546452025, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "10430": {"changesets": [{"author": "Jason Orendorff \u003cjorendorff@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1491924 - Split test-macosx64/debug-jsreftest-e10s across 3 chunks rather than 2, to stop timeouts. r=jmaher, a=test-only\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D14763", "files": ["taskcluster/ci/test/reftest.yml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8c684af09a0a4f019cc8627d168b9f4b175eec42", "parents": ["23df5870b62ded06704a9a1fd4d7e3a4c5e525c5"], "tags": []}, {"author": "James Graham \u003cjames@hoppipolla.co.uk\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1440984 - Stop importing testharness into a support file. r=ato, a=test-only\n\nThis isn't a supported behaviour and may be responsible for the observed intermittents.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D14959", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/html/browsers/browsing-the-web/history-traversal/support/window-name-test.sub.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "611bf2bc713d21c405094e47d94f446e8ab68664", "parents": ["8c684af09a0a4f019cc8627d168b9f4b175eec42"], "tags": []}, {"author": "James Graham \u003cjames@hoppipolla.co.uk\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1440984 - Remove stale wpt metadata. r=aryx, a=test-only\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D15581", "files": ["testing/web-platform/meta/html/browsers/browsing-the-web/history-traversal/window-name-after-cross-origin-aux-frame-navigation.sub.html.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3b399bd35f3738467209b182df03c560bf3a6b02", "parents": ["611bf2bc713d21c405094e47d94f446e8ab68664"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jan de Mooij \u003cjdemooij@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1480121 - Remove the global stored in nsXPCWrappedJS. r=bzbarsky, a=RyanVM\n\nReasons for doing this:\n\n* nsXPCWrappedJS has complicated GC behavior and we're seeing some oranges in this area.\n\n* Due to the GC/CC complexity, the global stored in nsXPCWrappedJS *must be* the\n  object's global in the root-wrapper (implies non-CCW) case. If we do that, the\n  global is redundant because we can just get it from the object when we need it.\n\n* For the CCW case, it probably doesn't matter too much which chrome global we\n  use so we can use the compartment's first global - we now have an API for that.\n  This may also save some memory because it avoids keeping globals alive unnecessarily\n  and matches what we do for WrappedNatives and CCWs now. Furthermore, bug 1478359\n  comment 12 suggests CCWs can only show up here for in-content XBL and that's in the\n  process of being removed.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D15096", "files": ["js/src/jsfriendapi.cpp", "js/src/jsfriendapi.h", "js/src/vm/Compartment.h", "js/xpconnect/idl/nsIXPConnect.idl", "js/xpconnect/src/XPCWrappedJS.cpp", "js/xpconnect/src/xpcprivate.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ef2cd013fe73a216735629f5fab931c6ccbdd29d", "parents": ["3b399bd35f3738467209b182df03c560bf3a6b02"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Henri Sivonen \u003chsivonen@hsivonen.fi\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1512758. r=smaug, a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D14141", "files": ["dom/base/nsContentUtils.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c511b04377a198c6da03b32ea27e7d042e75fda1", "parents": ["ef2cd013fe73a216735629f5fab931c6ccbdd29d"], "tags": []}], "date": 1546469621, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "10431": {"changesets": [{"author": "dlee \u003cdlee@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1504774 - Fix url-classifier worker thread is not aborted while shutting down. r=francois, a=RyanVM\n\nIn Bug 1453038, |mUpdateInterrupted| is set in Classifer::Close() which is\ncalled by PreShutdown to abort an ongoing update. That doesn't handle\nall the cases.\n\nThe SafeBrowsing update involves two threads, worker thread, and update\nthread. Update thread takes care of most of the update work, when it finishes\nits task, it posts a task back to the worker thread to apply the updated database\nand also do some cleanup stuff. Then the update is complete.\n\nThe fix in Bug 1453038 doesn't abort an update if the woker thread is doing\nthe job. This is because the |mUpdateInterrupted| flag is set in the\nworker thread. The PreShutdown event which eventually sets the flag has to\nwait until the worker thread's current task is done.\n\nIn this patch:\n1. Check nsUrlClassifierDBService::ShutdownHasStarted() to abort shutdown.\nThis is set by main thread so both worker thread and update thread can\nbe interrupted now.\n2. mIsClosed is now replaced by the mUpdateInterrupted. The semantics of\nmUpdateInterrupted is now changed to abort update for any internal APIs\nwhich should cause an update to abort.\n3. Remove |mUpdateInterrupted| and |ShutdownHasStarted()| checks and\nunify with |ShouldAbort()|\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D12229", "files": ["toolkit/components/url-classifier/Classifier.cpp", "toolkit/components/url-classifier/Classifier.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b168e29f3c821f8d170d99c42bec442eb32351de", "parents": ["c511b04377a198c6da03b32ea27e7d042e75fda1"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Michael Kaply \u003cmozilla@kaply.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1510296 - Update Google search for new codes. r=daleharvey, a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D13087", "files": ["browser/components/search/searchplugins/google-2018.xml", "browser/components/search/searchplugins/google-b-1-d.xml", "browser/components/search/searchplugins/google-b-1-e.xml", "browser/components/search/searchplugins/google-b-d.xml", "browser/components/search/searchplugins/google-b-e.xml", "browser/components/search/searchplugins/google.xml", "browser/components/search/searchplugins/images/google.ico", "browser/components/search/searchplugins/list.json", "browser/components/search/test/browser/browser_google.js", "browser/components/search/test/browser/browser_google_behavior.js", "mobile/android/components/search/searchplugins/google-b-1-m.xml", "mobile/android/components/search/searchplugins/google-b-m.xml", "mobile/android/components/search/searchplugins/list.json", "toolkit/components/search/nsSearchService.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fea77d171e0f3de696f7525018a1da062aab22e5", "parents": ["b168e29f3c821f8d170d99c42bec442eb32351de"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Haik Aftandilian \u003chaftandilian@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1508277 - Crash in mozilla::gl::SurfaceFactory_IOSurface::CreateShared. r=Alex_Gaynor, a=RyanVM\n\nAllow access to device-id and vendor-id IOKit properties needed for AppleIntelHD3000GraphicsGLDriver.\n\nFixes a crash in the AppleIntelHD3000GraphicsGLDriver userland driver which is used in some 2011-era Macs.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D15528", "files": ["security/sandbox/mac/SandboxPolicies.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2f7653477756a0d4ecac6296d98b09c846d594a5", "parents": ["fea77d171e0f3de696f7525018a1da062aab22e5"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Erica Wright \u003cewright@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1512166 - Show blocked labels by default, hide when there's an exception. r=nhnt11, a=RyanVM\n\nIn the control panel, show the blocking category labels for tracking protection and cookie restrictions. Hide the label if the user has set an exception for that page.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D15212", "files": ["browser/app/profile/firefox.js", "browser/themes/shared/controlcenter/panel.inc.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c0660dad5c7eebbdace7667db4b1f24098dadcc3", "parents": ["2f7653477756a0d4ecac6296d98b09c846d594a5"], "tags": []}], "date": 1546474166, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "10432": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\ncs -\u003e f797d757da5f\nen-GB -\u003e a916f3f7c67b\nes-MX -\u003e a0be6722b4f4\nfr -\u003e f730237985d9\nro -\u003e e749a62c6f02", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e8984e5b21d48cc5b47aaf458c2a76ff288443be", "parents": ["c0660dad5c7eebbdace7667db4b1f24098dadcc3"], "tags": []}, {"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Firefox l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\ncak -\u003e 3cfc5bd86aac\ncs -\u003e f797d757da5f\nen-GB -\u003e a916f3f7c67b\nes-MX -\u003e a0be6722b4f4\nfr -\u003e f730237985d9\nit -\u003e 8eb842650936\nro -\u003e e749a62c6f02", "files": ["browser/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "24b9264471c74c9ec6040a4a3a9fdc751060e772", "parents": ["e8984e5b21d48cc5b47aaf458c2a76ff288443be"], "tags": []}], "date": 1546502425, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "10433": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Firefox l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\nfr -\u003e ebafbe47db71\nia -\u003e b47ae8235e2b", "files": ["browser/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a167eb54b3b235db570efd236ea584e5e1e628c4", "parents": ["24b9264471c74c9ec6040a4a3a9fdc751060e772"], "tags": []}], "date": 1546527621, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "10434": {"changesets": [{"author": "ffxbld \u003cffxbld@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No Bug, mozilla-beta repo-update HSTS HPKP blocklist remote-settings - a=repo-update r=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D15644", "files": ["browser/app/blocklist.xml", "security/manager/ssl/StaticHPKPins.h", "security/manager/ssl/nsSTSPreloadList.inc", "services/settings/dumps/blocklists/addons.json", "services/settings/dumps/main/language-dictionaries.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0ed7bf6707553ca54c207c96c9ad814ad0bb8096", "parents": ["a167eb54b3b235db570efd236ea584e5e1e628c4"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jon Coppeard \u003cjcoppeard@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1516138 - Check GC zeal mode is in range. r=allstars.chh, a=NPOTB", "files": ["js/src/gc/GC.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6ec9d5db308ead94198ed2f9e3cc9dc4c3546234", "parents": ["0ed7bf6707553ca54c207c96c9ad814ad0bb8096"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Timothy Nikkel \u003ctnikkel@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1511603. Ignore grayscale color profiles in webp images because webp images are never grayscale. r=aosmond, a=RyanVM", "files": ["image/decoders/nsWebPDecoder.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2ec4c1f9e95d51e1f356151e57b1ae47224c48c7", "parents": ["6ec9d5db308ead94198ed2f9e3cc9dc4c3546234"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Lars T Hansen \u003clhansen@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1516720 - Make an overbroad assertion narrower. r=jseward, a=RyanVM\n\nWe use a cmpxchg loop on x86 / x64 systems to implement bitwise\nread-modify-write atomic operations.  This means that we can use\nword-width operations even when we're operating on sub-wordsize data,\nso there's no reason to force the RMW operand into a byte-wide\nregister - only the registers used for the memory access need be\nspecial on x86, since memory accesses must still be word-wide.\n\nThus the assertion that asserts that the value must be in a byte\nregister applies only to ADD and SUB (since they use XADD and require\na byte register).", "files": ["js/src/jit/x86-shared/MacroAssembler-x86-shared.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "35ba72605a9aba2f4d8cb9b0d024c73395b2536e", "parents": ["2ec4c1f9e95d51e1f356151e57b1ae47224c48c7"], "tags": ["DEVEDITION_65_0b8_BUILD1", "DEVEDITION_65_0b8_RELEASE", "FENNEC_65_0b8_BUILD1", "FENNEC_65_0b8_RELEASE", "FIREFOX_65_0b8_BUILD1", "FIREFOX_65_0b8_RELEASE"]}], "date": 1546527837, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "10435": {"changesets": [{"author": "Mozilla Releng Treescript \u003crelease+treescript@mozilla.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug - Tagging 35ba72605a9aba2f4d8cb9b0d024c73395b2536e with FENNEC_65_0b8_BUILD1 a=release CLOSED TREE DONTBUILD", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "945390fae56e0e45d71f6f2d1c41d59fd0383940", "parents": ["35ba72605a9aba2f4d8cb9b0d024c73395b2536e"], "tags": []}], "date": 1546537729, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "10436": {"changesets": [{"author": "Mozilla Releng Treescript \u003crelease+treescript@mozilla.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug - Tagging 35ba72605a9aba2f4d8cb9b0d024c73395b2536e with DEVEDITION_65_0b8_BUILD1 a=release CLOSED TREE DONTBUILD", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7b9f189441d4f6cc5b6311ad31f56f0f943b65bc", "parents": ["945390fae56e0e45d71f6f2d1c41d59fd0383940"], "tags": []}], "date": 1546538026, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "10437": {"changesets": [{"author": "Mozilla Releng Treescript \u003crelease+treescript@mozilla.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug - Tagging 35ba72605a9aba2f4d8cb9b0d024c73395b2536e with FIREFOX_65_0b8_BUILD1 a=release CLOSED TREE DONTBUILD", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0921acd257103bcd7d9b5a