b9d91be3dda\npt-BR -\u003e 25735cffb97b\nsk -\u003e 2110857e3bff\nth -\u003e a5d15b4327ee\ntr -\u003e 46ae87a0ab99\nzh-CN -\u003e a8f0b91b2ffc", "files": ["browser/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ee0890efbe44ff3062c0ab32d6bdd8d2be722c1f", "parents": ["6b8d1dfbd977c56a399c27d1df553209c779e290"], "tags": []}], "date": 1547276430, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "10496": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\nda -\u003e be0d02a86594\nnl -\u003e bd34ad295086\npl -\u003e 30def7b1330f", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "00c3c07eae79756b3bd8ef79e17dbf1a35ea81c2", "parents": ["ee0890efbe44ff3062c0ab32d6bdd8d2be722c1f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Firefox l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\nda -\u003e be0d02a86594\nfa -\u003e cd2a61072fac\nnl -\u003e bd34ad295086\npl -\u003e 30def7b1330f\nvi -\u003e a86a5b40d603", "files": ["browser/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f169ecb08260930d1dabf3b51533fea2822c6066", "parents": ["00c3c07eae79756b3bd8ef79e17dbf1a35ea81c2"], "tags": []}], "date": 1547280027, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "10497": {"changesets": [{"author": "James Willcox \u003csnorp@snorp.net\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1354200 - Exit instead of MOZ_CRASH on channel error in child process. r=jld, a=jcristau\n\nAndroid mercilessly kills the parent in low memory situations, and we\ndon't want that to trigger a crash when the child is abruptly\ndisconnected.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D16234", "files": ["ipc/glue/MessageChannel.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "58340264bdac2c86845f2cb2d29877016e155c6d", "parents": ["f169ecb08260930d1dabf3b51533fea2822c6066"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Tim D. Smith \u003ctdsmith@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1519170 - Re-renew GEOLOCATION_REQUEST_GRANTED probe. r=chutten, a=RyanVM\n\nThe `GEOLOCATION_REQUEST_GRANTED` probe was renewed in Bug #1494496 to support targeting for a survey project that I originally expected to launch in November. Thanks to the usual vagaries of IRBs, holidays, and other priorities, we haven't launched yet, and the probe expiry is configured to stop collecting in 65. To mitigate the risk of failing to deploy the survey before the targeting probe expires, I'd like to bump the probe expiration out another couple of releases and uplift to beta.\n\nI think we're actually ready to launch now so I'm confident another 12 weeks will be more than enough time and we won't have to repeat this exercise again.\n\nI expect the data review in Bug #1494496 provides coverage for this change.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D16211", "files": ["toolkit/components/telemetry/Histograms.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5eeab947d0ff48e6340bbc6bedbb0f1ec774c707", "parents": ["58340264bdac2c86845f2cb2d29877016e155c6d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Dragana Damjanovic \u003cdd.mozilla@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1514688 - In case we already have a h2 connection and it does not support websockets, we should not try again to use websockets over h2. r=michal, a=RyanVM\n\nThere are 2 parts of the patch:\n1) we should not try to use websockets over h2 if we already know that they are not supported.\n2) make sure that we clean up websockets waiting for the settings frame when we close a h2 connection. (the part 1) will fix the issue, this part is only to be 100% that we some how do not retrigger the issue)\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D15296", "files": ["netwerk/protocol/http/Http2Session.cpp", "netwerk/protocol/http/nsHttpConnectionMgr.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "07265912b0c7eaccbe864f27f3b1ac60b4831700", "parents": ["5eeab947d0ff48e6340bbc6bedbb0f1ec774c707"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mark Striemer \u003cmstriemer@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1486507 - Record telemetry for browser language changes. r=rpl,flod,chutten, a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D11795", "files": ["browser/components/preferences/browserLanguages.js", "browser/components/preferences/in-content/main.js", "browser/components/preferences/in-content/tests/browser_browser_languages_subdialog.js", "toolkit/components/telemetry/Events.yaml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a902a8dcea8d2d51debed83ddf0f589ae4c88129", "parents": ["07265912b0c7eaccbe864f27f3b1ac60b4831700"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Dan Minor \u003cdminor@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1439997 - Remove old mac video capture code. r=jib, a=RyanVM\n\nThis code is no longer used and has been removed upstream. We can remove\nit as well.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D15196", "files": ["media/webrtc/trunk/webrtc/modules/video_capture/mac/avfoundation/video_capture_avfoundation.h", "media/webrtc/trunk/webrtc/modules/video_capture/mac/avfoundation/video_capture_avfoundation.mm", "media/webrtc/trunk/webrtc/modules/video_capture/mac/avfoundation/video_capture_avfoundation_info.h", "media/webrtc/trunk/webrtc/modules/video_capture/mac/avfoundation/video_capture_avfoundation_info.mm", "media/webrtc/trunk/webrtc/modules/video_capture/mac/avfoundation/video_capture_avfoundation_info_objc.h", "media/webrtc/trunk/webrtc/modules/video_capture/mac/avfoundation/video_capture_avfoundation_info_objc.mm", "media/webrtc/trunk/webrtc/modules/video_capture/mac/avfoundation/video_capture_avfoundation_objc.h", "media/webrtc/trunk/webrtc/modules/video_capture/mac/avfoundation/video_capture_avfoundation_objc.mm", "media/webrtc/trunk/webrtc/modules/video_capture/mac/avfoundation/video_capture_avfoundation_utility.h", "media/webrtc/trunk/webrtc/modules/video_capture/mac/video_capture_mac.mm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9104a4e2e3a4670bb75334e3ab1994f7728362b9", "parents": ["a902a8dcea8d2d51debed83ddf0f589ae4c88129"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Dan Minor \u003cdminor@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1439997 - Fix ondevicechange event on OS X. r=jib, a=RyanVM\n\nThis brings the changes from Bug 1286429 that were made to the older\nmac/avfoundation video capture code to the newer objc video capture\ncode.\n\nDepends on D15196\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D15197", "files": ["media/webrtc/trunk/webrtc/modules/video_capture/objc/device_info.h", "media/webrtc/trunk/webrtc/modules/video_capture/objc/device_info.mm", "media/webrtc/trunk/webrtc/modules/video_capture/objc/device_info_objc.h", "media/webrtc/trunk/webrtc/modules/video_capture/objc/device_info_objc.mm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b295af2ecf44a671a7802d6de183a7a5a03c259d", "parents": ["9104a4e2e3a4670bb75334e3ab1994f7728362b9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Dan Minor \u003cdminor@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1518744 - Deregister owner in DeviceInfoIos destructor. r=jib, a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D16047", "files": ["media/webrtc/trunk/webrtc/modules/video_capture/objc/device_info.mm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c0445e5ce38871a960e29fa97a6992df24b0bd50", "parents": ["b295af2ecf44a671a7802d6de183a7a5a03c259d"], "tags": []}], "date": 1547316511, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "10498": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\nit -\u003e 768f6e4ede0a\nkab -\u003e 00bc59c3b9dd\nnl -\u003e 08c28c215b23\nta -\u003e 52b07725a1be", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5bd8d895c5e5ae81f0852db02cc930c2c9ada6b8", "parents": ["c0445e5ce38871a960e29fa97a6992df24b0bd50"], "tags": []}, {"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Firefox l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\nit -\u003e 768f6e4ede0a\nja -\u003e ff5afb7f6ca3\nja-JP-mac -\u003e 6d7522a1dec8\nka -\u003e 2e0c73eb23a4\nkab -\u003e 00bc59c3b9dd\nnl -\u003e e6fb402e28a4\nsl -\u003e fea892373d48\nta -\u003e c8040e12fe14\nth -\u003e 9fe31a6c632f", "files": ["browser/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1d823b3ee5adc7541d54e1484d4bdd8ef963de35", "parents": ["5bd8d895c5e5ae81f0852db02cc930c2c9ada6b8"], "tags": []}], "date": 1547323225, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "10499": {"changesets": [{"author": "Andrei Lazar \u003candrei.a.lazar@softvision.ro\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1505720 - Crash [@ java.lang.NullPointerException: at org.mozilla.gecko.fxa.authenticator.AndroidFxAccount.renameAccountIfNecessary(AndroidFxAccount.java)]. r=Grisha, a=RyanVM\n\nRefreshing account (triggered by signing in) can cause a NullPointerException after quickly signing out.\nThis defect consists in bad sync between the signing in state and signing out state.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D14269", "files": ["mobile/android/services/src/main/java/org/mozilla/gecko/fxa/authenticator/AndroidFxAccount.java"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "35180dd24536b073adc5fb42946a80c556f6a5d0", "parents": ["1d823b3ee5adc7541d54e1484d4bdd8ef963de35"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Emily Toop \u003cetoop@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1509271 - Ensure that `UpdateRootFrameMetrics` is called even if the GeckoView embedding app is not using the `AndroidDynamicToolbarAnimator`. r=kats, a=RyanVM\n\nWhen selected text in `geckoview_example`, the text selection toolbar was always positioned in the top left corner of the screen, regardless of where in the page the text was selected.\n\nThe cause of the bug was that UpdateRootFrameMetrics was being called only if the app utilised the `AndroidDynamicToolbar`. This caused the `mViewportZoom` value inside `GeckoSession` to always be 0. When using the `clientToFrameMatrix` function to place the text selection toolbar on screen, the generated matrix was incorrect as the zoom value was 0, causing the resulting frame to be offset by the zoom value.\n\nBy ensuring that `UpdateRootFrameMetrics` is called inside `AsyncCompositionManager`even when there is no `AndroidDynamicToolbarAnimator` this zoom value is correctly set and the resulting frame for the text selection toolbar is correctly placed.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D15941", "files": ["gfx/layers/composite/AsyncCompositionManager.cpp", "gfx/layers/ipc/UiCompositorControllerParent.cpp", "gfx/layers/ipc/UiCompositorControllerParent.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9a0b078546bd21aabdc056dfb6a08e8594565d88", "parents": ["35180dd24536b073adc5fb42946a80c556f6a5d0"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Adam Gashlin \u003cagashlin@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1514501 - Fix screen selection and scaling for fullscreen. r=jmathies, a=RyanVM\n\nI needed to scale the layout device pixels coming from Windows before passing them to ScreenForRect(). Also, I'm using GetRect() directly instead of GetRectDisplayPix() * scale now, to avoid an unnecessary double scale & round which was making fullscreen windows off by one pixel in many cases.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D15604", "files": ["widget/windows/nsWindow.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "694ef5b65db8c5e3570e6e1a9bee47608b4d3ba9", "parents": ["9a0b078546bd21aabdc056dfb6a08e8594565d88"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Tom Tromey \u003ctom@tromey.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1517433 - Do not assert on over-long float printf. r=froydnj, a=RyanVM\n\nmozilla::PrintfTarget::cvt_f release asserts that the desired printf\nfit into a statically-sized buffer.  However, this may not be the case\nif the user requested a larger width or precision.  Handle this\nunusual case by allocating a temporary buffer.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 2WicecHDzDR\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D15989", "files": ["mozglue/misc/Printf.cpp", "mozglue/tests/TestPrintf.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "60be2a80ee0e8c213d16a192780a9f70ac6f5d5a", "parents": ["694ef5b65db8c5e3570e6e1a9bee47608b4d3ba9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Dragana Damjanovic \u003cdd.mozilla@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1515459 - Check if we reenter CreateShimError. r=mayhemer, a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D15297", "files": ["netwerk/protocol/http/TunnelUtils.cpp", "netwerk/protocol/http/TunnelUtils.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "da0b07a8386c07b7b4c54a5c001fbedc64fa79eb", "parents": ["60be2a80ee0e8c213d16a192780a9f70ac6f5d5a"], "tags": []}], "date": 1547323890, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "10500": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\nda -\u003e aa0c4049abaa", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "371b3ceabd5ad8568cff2af7255543e2a141d6d2", "parents": ["da0b07a8386c07b7b4c54a5c001fbedc64fa79eb"], "tags": []}, {"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Firefox l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\nda -\u003e aa0c4049abaa", "files": ["browser/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "80ab023e1d8eb9f1fbc7d26e3774ef9aebb7dcdb", "parents": ["371b3ceabd5ad8568cff2af7255543e2a141d6d2"], "tags": []}], "date": 1547326825, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "10501": {"changesets": [{"author": "Xidorn Quan \u003cme@upsuper.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1514498 - Hide rather than collapse scrollbar thumb when scrollbar is disabled. r=NeilDeakin, a=RyanVM\n\nCollapsing thumb causes frame of scrollbar to cache an incorrect pref\nsize, which makes it not able to appear in certain cases.\n\nThis patch changes it to use \"visibility: hidden\" instead so that the\nthumb is hidden but still contributes to the width of scrollbar.\n\nAn alternative would be also change the code in nsScrollbarFrame to set\nsomething other than collapsed attribute instead, but I'm not sure\nwhether doing that is any better than just adding a rule. We need the\nrule anyway regardless of what we set on the element.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D15244", "files": ["layout/reftests/css-scrollbars/reftest.list", "layout/reftests/css-scrollbars/scrollbar-thin-overflow-change-ref.html", "layout/reftests/css-scrollbars/scrollbar-thin-overflow-change.html", "toolkit/content/minimal-xul.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7ddc13a7de8d8d42546f96b5a14379c4ca49dfde", "parents": ["80ab023e1d8eb9f1fbc7d26e3774ef9aebb7dcdb"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrew McCreight \u003ccontinuation@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1517577 - DataTransferItemList::Add should use nsVariantCC. r=nika, a=RyanVM\n\nnsVariant isn't cycle collected, so this can cause a leak.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D16124", "files": ["dom/events/DataTransferItemList.cpp", "testing/web-platform/meta/FileAPI/file/__dir__.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/html/semantics/forms/form-submission-0/__dir__.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "75bae5cabb1c83c4a0333663d1db9c4079130880", "parents": ["7ddc13a7de8d8d42546f96b5a14379c4ca49dfde"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Eric Rahm \u003cerahm@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1519209 - Disable NSS_ALLOW_SSLKEYLOGFILE in beta and release. r=glandium, a=RyanVM\n\nThis disables NSS_ALLOW_SSLKEYLOGFILE in beta in release in order to avoid shutdown hangs until the NSS project has time to fix the root cause of the issue.", "files": ["python/mozbuild/mozbuild/frontend/gyp_reader.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "138a3eb773c865898c1f43e53aa9b3b39e2f38d4", "parents": ["75bae5cabb1c83c4a0333663d1db9c4079130880"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Johann Hofmann \u003cjhofmann@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1519137 - Add lazy pref getter for content blocking before initializing blockers. r=ewright, a=RyanVM\n\nThis was causing some prefs that blockers were accessing not to be set yet.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D16208", "files": ["browser/base/content/browser-contentblocking.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d566c5f82f8b4d53ed05bc8836ea0b9d7dee051c", "parents": ["138a3eb773c865898c1f43e53aa9b3b39e2f38d4"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrew McCreight \u003ccontinuation@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1517071 - Clear AsyncWaitRunnable::mStream when cancelled. r=froydnj, a=RyanVM\n\nAsyncWaitRunnable holds a strong reference to its stream, and\nNonBlockingAsyncInputStream holds a strong reference to the\nrunnable. The cycle gets broken in the RunAsyncWaitCallback() method\nof the stream, but if the runnable is cancelled then we leak them\nboth. This patch fixes that by clearing the pointer to the stream when\nthe runnable is cancelled, breaking the cycle.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D16248", "files": ["testing/web-platform/meta/FileAPI/FileReader/__dir__.ini", "xpcom/io/NonBlockingAsyncInputStream.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5b52f9f8300439f6f58beead39f28ee22faf4863", "parents": ["d566c5f82f8b4d53ed05bc8836ea0b9d7dee051c"], "tags": []}], "date": 1547329265, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "10502": {"changesets": [{"author": "Oriol Brufau \u003coriol-bugzilla@hotmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1515447 - Add receiver parameter to Debugger.Object's getProperty and setProperty. r=jimb, a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D15018", "files": ["js/src/doc/Debugger/Debugger.Object.md", "js/src/jit-test/tests/debug/Object-getProperty-03.js", "js/src/jit-test/tests/debug/Object-setProperty-03.js", "js/src/vm/Debugger.cpp", "js/src/vm/Debugger.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7bfd0ddce88e35eb5be95af2f62d7a50208b0741", "parents": ["5b52f9f8300439f6f58beead39f28ee22faf4863"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Oriol Brufau \u003coriol-bugzilla@hotmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1515046 - Add receiverId parameter in objectClient.getPropertyValue. r=nchevobbe, a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D15788", "files": ["devtools/client/shared/components/reps/reps.js", "devtools/server/actors/object.js", "devtools/server/tests/unit/test_objectgrips-fn-apply-01.js", "devtools/server/tests/unit/test_objectgrips-fn-apply-02.js", "devtools/server/tests/unit/test_objectgrips-fn-apply-03.js", "devtools/server/tests/unit/test_objectgrips-property-value-01.js", "devtools/server/tests/unit/test_objectgrips-property-value-02.js", "devtools/server/tests/unit/test_objectgrips-property-value-03.js", "de