efault", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\nen-CA -\u003e 1df3b5370c30\nes-CL -\u003e ff997f81eae6\nes-MX -\u003e 7d161fdf265c\neu -\u003e 506f20acd46d\nhi-IN -\u003e 504d2fde3fc7\nhu -\u003e 6477fd6ddf64\nmai -\u003e d524e539eefb\nnn-NO -\u003e 656adee29da6\nsq -\u003e f7c2ccfb7710\nta -\u003e 047b3e205cca\nur -\u003e 03708a03f1b8\nzh-CN -\u003e b9c275f71f13\nzh-TW -\u003e f2b2ea4cd960", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ac40678709f6f3af82e30819cea10260b6e497fc", "parents": ["19af0fe7d76ebd6f2c44bf8c69ef57e1386a25fb"], "tags": []}, {"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Firefox l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\ncak -\u003e 3bd3d9938de2\nen-CA -\u003e 1df3b5370c30\nes-CL -\u003e ff997f81eae6\nes-MX -\u003e 7d161fdf265c\neu -\u003e 506f20acd46d\nhi-IN -\u003e 504d2fde3fc7\nhu -\u003e 6477fd6ddf64\nlij -\u003e 3da1a4467c53\nmai -\u003e d524e539eefb\nnn-NO -\u003e 656adee29da6\nsq -\u003e f7c2ccfb7710\nta -\u003e 047b3e205cca\nur -\u003e 03708a03f1b8\nzh-CN -\u003e b9c275f71f13\nzh-TW -\u003e f2b2ea4cd960", "files": ["browser/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "383deda87e7b30176866a1ca18be59895dc59acd", "parents": ["ac40678709f6f3af82e30819cea10260b6e497fc"], "tags": []}], "date": 1547470827, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "10511": {"changesets": [{"author": "ffxbld \u003cffxbld@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No Bug, mozilla-beta repo-update HSTS HPKP blocklist remote-settings - a=repo-update r=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D16454", "files": ["browser/app/blocklist.xml", "security/manager/ssl/StaticHPKPins.h", "security/manager/ssl/nsSTSPreloadList.inc", "services/settings/dumps/blocklists/addons.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6e759841cfad41500c7f82936d4f28b3818fc99d", "parents": ["383deda87e7b30176866a1ca18be59895dc59acd"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kestrel \u003cke5trel@protonmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1514715 - Update color prefs for new color IDs including -moz-win-accentcolor. r=jmathies, a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D14723", "files": ["widget/nsXPLookAndFeel.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "192563fa86235b783669e8c0ce624a59eec0f708", "parents": ["6e759841cfad41500c7f82936d4f28b3818fc99d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Razvan Caliman \u003crcaliman@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1510790 - Introduce Redux selector for tracked changes to return the nested tree structure. r=pbro, a=RyanVM\n\nThis patch introduces a Redux selector for the Changes slice. A selector here is a fancy word for a method that returns a subset from the state without having to expose the state's structure to the consumer. It is also useful for returning a derived version of the state which we're using here.\n\nThe tracked changed CSS rules in the Redux state are not stored in a nested structure. A shallow structure is easier to query and to work with in our use case. But the Changes panel needs to display CSS rules in a hierarchical structure (ex: a style rule which is a child of a @media rule). To do this, the React component used to build up the nested structure as it consumed the changes from the Redux state. To prevent rendering duplicates of rules (once as part of an ancestor's children and once as a standalone rule), the React component kept a reference of rules it had previously rendered. This had a flaw because it didn't account for the rule's stylesheet. The problem was that rules with identical selectors from different stylesheets would not all be rendered because they would be accidentally marked as previously rendered.\n\nThis is too much knowledge of the business logic for the React component anyway.\n\nThe Redux state should present itself in a way that's simple for the React component to consume. Hence the introduction of the `getChangesTree()` selector in this patch. This method allows us to present a comfortable structure to React while keeping the Redux structure comfortable for us to work with. This separation enables increased flexibility to restructure the Redux state without impacting the React components.\n\nMore about Redux selectors here: https://redux.js.org/recipes/computing-derived-data\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D16068", "files": ["devtools/client/inspector/changes/components/ChangesApp.js", "devtools/client/inspector/changes/moz.build", "devtools/client/inspector/changes/reducers/changes.js", "devtools/client/inspector/changes/selectors/changes.js", "devtools/client/inspector/changes/selectors/moz.build", "devtools/client/inspector/changes/test/browser.ini", "devtools/client/inspector/changes/test/browser_changes_declaration_identical_rules.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "aa0bf52184e60befc3b47a83d252aafdc13df34e", "parents": ["192563fa86235b783669e8c0ce624a59eec0f708"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Martin Stransky \u003cstransky@redhat.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1517074 - [Linux/Gtk] Enable native (xdg-desktop based) file dialog on KDE only due to Gtk+ regression. r=jhorak, a=RyanVM\n\nAlso add widget.allow-gtk-native-file-chooser preference value to force enable on all systems.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D16184", "files": ["widget/gtk/nsFilePicker.cpp", "widget/gtk/nsFilePicker.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "25ba8700fe9477fc7091067e79a2b281aeb0aa29", "parents": ["aa0bf52184e60befc3b47a83d252aafdc13df34e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Marco Bonardo \u003cmbonardo@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1519060 - Places maintenance doesn't properly replace malformed databases. r=Standard8, a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D16199", "files": ["toolkit/components/contentprefs/ContentPrefService2.js", "toolkit/components/places/PlacesDBUtils.jsm", "toolkit/components/places/tests/maintenance/corruptPayload.sqlite", "toolkit/components/places/tests/maintenance/test_integrity_replacement.js", "toolkit/components/places/tests/maintenance/xpcshell.ini", "toolkit/components/places/tests/migration/places_v43.sqlite", "toolkit/components/places/tests/unit/missingBuiltIn.sqlite", "toolkit/modules/Sqlite.jsm", "toolkit/modules/tests/xpcshell/test_sqlite.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1ee1bd77fa1c6fec07e4eda0d2fd52cf93ab9ab7", "parents": ["25ba8700fe9477fc7091067e79a2b281aeb0aa29"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Johann Hofmann \u003cjhofmann@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1519164 - Update content blocking UI tour url. r=nhnt11, a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D16288", "files": ["browser/app/profile/firefox.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7448d41d4fdc5ae2ea6008ee1d71b83421a82832", "parents": ["1ee1bd77fa1c6fec07e4eda0d2fd52cf93ab9ab7"], "tags": []}], "date": 1547476034, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "10512": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\ncy -\u003e 096705579e69\neo -\u003e 17745df2374e\nes-AR -\u003e cff3cbb0a12f\nsl -\u003e 6b1ec1a84612", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "78ff07a1ff41052d69f96d906417ee2cc4051012", "parents": ["7448d41d4fdc5ae2ea6008ee1d71b83421a82832"], "tags": []}, {"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Firefox l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\ncy -\u003e c752e91ae4da\neo -\u003e 17745df2374e\nes-AR -\u003e cff3cbb0a12f\nfr -\u003e a70d4b51f666\nnb-NO -\u003e d2585bc89e68\nrm -\u003e 0a68575cd9ff\nsl -\u003e 6a3945c2534d", "files": ["browser/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fcd8db2c5ac685be39cee633b09f44231849ea04", "parents": ["78ff07a1ff41052d69f96d906417ee2cc4051012"], "tags": []}], "date": 1547481652, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "10513": {"changesets": [{"author": "Ryan VanderMeulen \u003cryanvm@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out changeset d05c6310d573 (bug 1509906) for increasing the severity of bug 1518863. r=Gijs, a=RyanVM", "files": ["browser/base/content/browser.js", "browser/base/content/tabbrowser.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8f38ca46fb4495a087734b8269a61a51c284e6da", "parents": ["fcd8db2c5ac685be39cee633b09f44231849ea04"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrei Oprea \u003candrei.br92@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1515411 - Disable Return to AMO for 65 Beta and Release. r=k88hudson, a=RyanVM\n\nThis adds an `exclude` field in local providers that allows to exclude specific messages by ID.\n\nTest Plan:\nIn a fresh Firefox profile. On OSX make sure this is launched from the Applications folder and not from the installer.\n\n\n\u003e in order to confirm RTAMO is enabled\n\n1. enable `browser.newtabpage.activity-stream.asrouter.devtoolsEnabled`\n2. set `browser.newtabpage.activity-stream.asrouter.providers.onboarding` to `{\"id\":\"onboarding\",\"type\":\"local\",\"localProvider\":\"OnboardingMessageProvider\",\"enabled\":true,\"exclude\":[]}`\n3. navigate to `about:newtab#asrouter` and scroll to the bottom\n4. click `Force attribution`\n5. navigate to `about:welcome` and confirm that the RTAMO message is shown\n\n\u003e in order to confirm RTAMO is disabled\n\n6. set `browser.newtabpage.activity-stream.asrouter.providers.onboarding` to `{\"id\":\"onboarding\",\"type\":\"local\",\"localProvider\":\"OnboardingMessageProvider\",\"enabled\":true,\"exclude\":[\"RETURN_TO_AMO_1\"]}`\n7. navigate to `about:welcome` and confirm that the FxA accounts page is shown and not RTAMO\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D16053", "files": ["browser/components/newtab/lib/ASRouter.jsm", "browser/components/newtab/lib/ASRouterTargeting.jsm", "browser/components/newtab/lib/ActivityStream.jsm", "browser/components/newtab/lib/OnboardingMessageProvider.jsm", "browser/components/newtab/test/unit/asrouter/ASRouterTargeting.test.js", "browser/components/newtab/test/unit/asrouter/MessageLoaderUtils.test.js", "browser/components/newtab/test/unit/content-src/components/ReturnToAMO.test.jsx", "browser/components/newtab/test/unit/content-src/components/StartupOverlay.test.jsx", "browser/components/newtab/test/unit/unit-entry.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4befe1a74031dbeb0f106449047f3f827fe45d7d", "parents": ["8f38ca46fb4495a087734b8269a61a51c284e6da"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Gijs Kruitbosch \u003cgijskruitbosch@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1518996 - Fix double border/outline for textbox[multiline] by not setting one on the inner textarea. r=jaws, a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D16334", "files": ["toolkit/themes/shared/in-content/common.inc.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "76325782999f2b06123ebbff85df059f3cab0696", "parents": ["4befe1a74031dbeb0f106449047f3f827fe45d7d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Gijs Kruitbosch \u003cgijskruitbosch@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1516767 - Adjust button border, outline and box-shadow to be compatible with High-Contrast Mode and less glitchy. r=jaws, a=RyanVM", "files": ["toolkit/themes/shared/in-content/common.inc.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3fa15331a2201b74baefa7120a599d5d70a85643", "parents": ["76325782999f2b06123ebbff85df059f3cab0696"], "tags": []}, {"author": "k88hudson \u003ck88hudson@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1518321 - Pref on CFR in release. r=andreio, a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D15880", "files": ["browser/app/profile/firefox.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "161822bbdcd274f0d67aa7c1a6913caeabf80aa6", "parents": ["3fa15331a2201b74baefa7120a599d5d70a85643"], "tags": []}, {"author": "D\u00e3o Gottwald \u003cdao@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1512493 - Make switching tabs by scrolling pref-controlled and off by default. r=stransky, a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D16021", "files": ["modules/libpref/init/all.js", "toolkit/content/jar.mn", "toolkit/content/widgets/tabbox.xml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8574d2808aaa0afa131cc57be70b86dad3398ff0", "parents": ["161822bbdcd274f0d67aa7c1a6913caeabf80aa6"], "tags": ["DEVEDITION_65_0b11_BUILD1", "DEVEDITION_65_0b11_RELEASE", "FENNEC_65_0b11_BUILD1", "FENNEC_65_0b11_RELEASE", "FIREFOX_65_0b11_BUILD1", "FIREFOX_65_0b11_RELEASE"]}], "date": 1547486611, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "10514": {"changesets": [{"author": "Mozilla Releng Treescript \u003crelease+treescript@mozilla.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug - Tagging 8574d2808aaa0afa131cc57be70b86dad3398ff0 with FENNEC_65_0b11_BUILD1 a=release CLOSED TREE DONTBUILD", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a7933955fab82df154215796d6a5332a63955787", "parents": ["8574d2808aaa0afa131cc57be70b86dad3398ff0"], "tags": []}], "date": 1547495959, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "10515": {"changesets": [{"author": "Mozilla Releng Treescript \u003crelease+treescript@mozilla.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug - Tagging 8574d2808aaa0afa131cc57be70b86dad3398ff0 with DEVEDITION_65_0b11_BUILD1 a=release CLOSED TREE DONTBUILD", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "bae4cea5111968906d8006210e7b21d75b2a79f3", "parents": ["a7933955fab82df154215796d6a5332a63955787"], "tags": []}], "date": 1547496272, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "10516": {"changesets": [{"author": "Mozilla Releng Treescript \u003crelease+treescript@mozilla.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug - Tagging 8574d2808aaa0afa131cc57be70b86dad3398ff0 with FIREFOX_65_0b11_BUILD1 a=release CLOSED TREE DONTBUILD", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d5596809608eeb558c6327379e4c1b17829a08f7", "parents": ["bae4cea5111968906d8006210e7b21d75b2a79f3"], "tags": []}], "date": 1547496494, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "10517": {"changesets": [{"author": "Ted Mielczarek \u003cted@mielczarek.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1517909 - Format build telemetry time correctly when seconds has no fractional component. r=nalexander a=NPOTB\n\nIt turns out that Python's `datetime.isoformat` method will leave off the\nfractional component of seconds if it would be all zeroes, but the voluptuous\n`Datetime` validator wants it to be present, so it's possible to hit an error\nif you run mach at exactly an integer second.\n\nThis patch switches from `isoformat` to `strftime` with an explicit format\nstring instead.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D15981", "files": ["python/mach/mach/test/test_telemetry.py", "python/mach/mach/test/zero_microseconds.py", "python/mozbuild/mozbuild/telemetry.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c4617240dec57c705301dad0044afb5b2a319a12", "parents": ["d5596809608eeb558c6327379e4c1b17829a08f7"], "tags": []}], "date": 1547534206, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "csabou@mozilla.com"}, "10518": {"changesets": [{"author": "Henrik Skupin \u003cmail@hskupin.info\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1478358 - [marionette] Don't wait for resize events in \"Set Window Rect\". r=ato a=test-only\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D16338", "files": ["testing/marionette/driver.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2d63cb7c2cccb8e0884a3ce2de06b43d9b6990ef", "parents": ["c4617240dec57c705301dad0044afb5b2a319a12"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Henrik Skupin \u003cmail@hskupin.info\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1478358 - [wdspec] Enforce a default window position for each session. r=ato a=test-only\n\nTo have the same pre-conditions for all wdspec tests, the session fixture\nhas to set a default window position.\n\nDepends on D16338\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D16340", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/webdriver/tests/support/defaults.py", "testing/web-platform/tests/webdriver/tests/support/fixtures.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c52783e0d7e1e3ca9463e36a6b3de2a5ed04a563", "parents": ["2d63cb7c2cccb8e0884a3ce2de06b43d9b6990ef"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Henrik Skupin \u003cmail@hskupin.info\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1478358 - [wdspec] Enhance tests for the \"Set Window Rect\" command. r=ato a=test-only\n\nDepends on D16340\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D16342", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/webdriver/tests/set_window_rect/set.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c3a3d5aadad26e7a4d97cd034871c94b2371c375", "parents": ["c52783e0d7e1e3ca9463e36a6b3de2a5ed04a563"], "tags": []}], "date": 1547550670, "git_changesets": [null, null, null], "user": "csabou@mozilla.com"}, "10519": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\nbe -\u003e 1e500c86640b\nbr -\u003e def1833a6c00\ncak -\u003e 52c5713f7f92\ncs -\u003